### Container API Test File
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code or manually with curl

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001/api

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/../health

### 1. Generate a new container (auto-assign color and number)
POST {{baseUrl}}/containers/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Holiday decorations - Christmas ornaments and lights"
}

### 2. Generate a new container with specific color and number
POST {{baseUrl}}/containers/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "color": "Red",
  "number": 1,
  "description": "Family photos from 2020-2023",
  "location_text": "Attic-Left-A2"
}

### 3. Generate another container
POST {{baseUrl}}/containers/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "color": "Blue",
  "number": 15,
  "description": "Tax documents 2020-2024"
}

### 4. Get all containers
GET {{baseUrl}}/containers

### 5. Get container by QR code
GET {{baseUrl}}/containers/Red-01

### 6. Get container by QR code (Blue-15)
GET {{baseUrl}}/containers/Blue-15

### 7. Update container
# Replace {container-id} with actual UUID from previous responses
PUT {{baseUrl}}/containers/{container-id}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Updated: Holiday decorations - Christmas and Halloween",
  "location_text": "Garage-A1"
}

### 8. Get items in container
# Replace {container-id} with actual UUID
GET {{baseUrl}}/containers/{container-id}/items

### 9. Delete container
# Replace {container-id} with actual UUID
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/containers/{container-id}

### 10. Try to generate duplicate container (should fail with 409)
POST {{baseUrl}}/containers/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "color": "Red",
  "number": 1,
  "description": "This should fail - Red-01 already exists"
}

### 11. Test invalid color
POST {{baseUrl}}/containers/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "color": "InvalidColor",
  "number": 1
}

### 12. Test invalid number
POST {{baseUrl}}/containers/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "color": "Red",
  "number": 100
}
